<TITLE> Court orders arrest of Tajul Islam Faruk </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June4 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court on Thursday issued an arrest warrant against Westmont Bangladesh Limited chairman Kazi Tajul Islam Faruk in an embezzlement case. Faruk had sued the then Awami League chief Sheikh Hasina, now prime minister, for alleged extortion in the Bhagabari barge- mounted power plant during the 2007-2008 military-installed caretaker government. Magistrate Konika Biswas of Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate' Court issued the order after hearing the case filed earlier in the day by Ali Akkas Nurani, local advertiser and consultant of Westmont Offshore Bangladesh The case stated that Faruk had misappropriated money and threatened to kill the Nurani. Faruk allegedly misappropriated $ 1 million in service fee by coaxing Kaising, managing director of Malaysia of Westmont company, into paying him. Later, the accused set loose criminals to plunder the Nurani's house and threatened to kill him as he demanded his money, the case alleged. To cover up his crime, he gad filed Tk 3 crore extortion case against Hasina, now the prime minister, with Tejgaon police Advocates Dulal Mitra, PK Abdur Rab and Mahububul Haq argued for the plaintiff. b
